# Conflict Tracker - Crontab Configuration
#
# To install:
#   1. Copy this file to your crontab:
#      crontab -e
#   2. Update the paths below to match your project location
#   3. Paste the cron lines into your crontab
#
# Requirements:
#   - Bird CLI must be installed and authenticated
#   - Python 3 must be available
#   - Scripts must be executable (chmod +x scripts/*.sh)

# Fetch Twitter data every 15 minutes
# Adjust the timing based on your rate limits and needs
*/15 * * * * cd /Users/guoruidong/conflict-tracker && ./scripts/fetch-twitter-data.sh >> logs/fetch.log 2>&1

# Fetch trending news every hour for ticker
0 * * * * cd /Users/guoruidong/conflict-tracker && ./scripts/fetch-trending.sh >> logs/trending.log 2>&1

# Optional: Fetch data every 30 minutes instead of every 15
# */30 * * * * cd /path/to/conflict-tracker && ./scripts/fetch-twitter-data.sh >> logs/fetch.log 2>&1

# Optional: Schedule specific times (e.g., every hour at :15 and :45)
# 15,45 * * * * cd /path/to/conflict-tracker && ./scripts/fetch-twitter-data.sh >> logs/fetch.log 2>&1

# Notes:
#   - Logs are written to logs/ directory (create it first)
#   - Check logs/fetch.log and logs/trending.log for debugging
#   - Bird CLI uses your browser session, so rate limits apply
#   - Start with longer intervals (30-60 min) and adjust as needed
